{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/networkmode"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NetworkMode"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each mode maps to a specific "},{"code":"Virtualization.framework","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device attachment type. The mode determines how the guest’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"network traffic is routed relative to the host and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"external network."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Choosing-a-Network-Mode","text":"Choosing a Network Mode","level":2},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mode"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Guest → Internet"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Host → Guest"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Entitlement"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/nat"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✓"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Via resolved IP"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"✓","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Own LAN IP"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"com.apple.vm.networking","type":"codeVoice"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✗"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"✗","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For host-guest communication without full network access,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" mode and communicate via the VirtIO socket"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device ("},{"code":"VZVirtioSocketDeviceConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"), which is always"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attached regardless of network mode."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bridged mode requires the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"com.apple.vm.networking"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"restricted entitlement, which must be requested from Apple","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Developer Technical Support.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Why-There-Is-No-Host-Only-Mode","text":"Why There Is No Host-Only Mode"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework provides three network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attachment types: "},{"code":"VZNATNetworkDeviceAttachment","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"VZBridgedNetworkDeviceAttachment","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":". None of these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implements host-only semantics directly."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A host-only mode would require a user-space virtual network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"switch built on top of "},{"code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handling raw Ethernet frames, DHCP, and packet routing — a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"substantial subsystem that would need its own lifecycle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"management and security hardening. Rather than ship a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"half-baked implementation or silently fall back to NAT"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(which would give VMs unintended internet access), this enum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only exposes modes that the Virtualization framework supports"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"natively."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need isolated host-guest communication, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the VirtIO socket device. If you need full IP networking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"between VMs, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on a dedicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"host-only network interface."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The network configuration mode for a virtual machine."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"enum","role":"symbol","title":"NetworkMode","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit11NetworkModeO","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"NetworkMode","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NetworkMode"}]},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Enumeration Cases","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/nat"],"anchor":"Enumeration-Cases"},{"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/init(from:)"],"anchor":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/Equatable-Implementations"],"anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/Se","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SE","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SQ","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SH","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s16SendableMetatypeP"]}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/s16SendableMetatypeP":{"type":"unresolvable","title":"Swift.SendableMetatype","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s16SendableMetatypeP"},"do